# Hair Hack — Agent Workflow

This project uses [addyosmani/agent-skills](https://github.com/addyosmani/agent-skills). Skills live in `.cursor/skills/` (symlinks to `.vendor/agent-skills/skills/`).

## Lifecycle

```
DEFINE → PLAN → BUILD → VERIFY → REVIEW → SHIP
/spec    /plan   /build  /test    /review   /ship
```

| Phase | Skill | Project doc |
|-------|-------|-------------|
| Define | `spec-driven-development` | `docs/SPEC.md` |
| Plan | `planning-and-task-breakdown` | `docs/PLAN.md` |
| Tasks | `planning-and-task-breakdown` | `docs/TASKS.md` |
| Build | `incremental-implementation` + `test-driven-development` | — |
| UI | `frontend-ui-engineering` | — |
| API | `api-and-interface-design` | — |
| Verify | `browser-testing-with-devtools` | — |
| Review | `code-review-and-quality` | — |
| Ship | `shipping-and-launch` + `security-and-hardening` | — |

## Rules

1. **Spec before code** — read `docs/SPEC.md` before non-trivial changes. Update the spec when scope changes.
2. **Surface assumptions** — list assumptions explicitly before implementing; ask when requirements conflict.
3. **Incremental slices** — one verifiable change at a time; run `npm run build` after each slice.
4. **No secrets in git** — `.env.local` only; never commit API keys.
5. **Medical disclaimer** — UI must state this is not medical advice; previews are illustrative only.

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev      # local dev
npm run build    # production build check
npm run lint     # lint
```

## Boundaries

- **Always:** validate uploads server-side; keep prompts in `src/lib/prompts.ts`; TypeScript strict.
- **Ask first:** new dependencies, schema/DB, payment, storing user photos, changing image model.
- **Never:** commit `.env.local`; remove error handling to ship faster; claim medical outcomes.
